Tax Evaders CD Produced 100 Million Euros for Hamburg, Welt Says

-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 
2011-10-17T19:16:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/tax-evaders-cd-produced-100-million-euros-for-hamburg-welt-says.html
The acquisition of a CD with data on
tax evaders from  Switzerland  in February 2010 allowed the city
of Hamburg,  Germany , to collect 100 million euros in taxes, Die
Welt reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the
investigation.  Taxable assets amounted to about 309 million euros, from
which Hamburg got about a third in tax, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julie Cruz in Frankfurt at 
 jcruz6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at   arummer@bloomberg.net  